# Credify Project Overview

This repository contains a Streamlit app that integrates with Supabase and the YouTube Data API.

## Entry points and key files

- Main multi-page app: [credify_app.py](mdc:credify_app.py)
- Auth helpers and login flows: [auth.py](mdc:auth.py)
- Standalone dashboard (legacy/alternate view): [dashboard.py](mdc:dashboard.py)
- Standalone ingestion tool: [add_to_supabase.py](mdc:add_to_supabase.py)
- Standalone claim flow: [claim_role.py](mdc:claim_role.py)
- Metrics aggregation utility script: [update_user_metrics.py](mdc:update_user_metrics.py)
- Demo scripts for manual testing:
  - [test_supabase.py](mdc:test_supabase.py)
  - [test_youtube_fetch.py](mdc:test_youtube_fetch.py)

## Data model (high-level)

- Tables expected in Supabase: `users`, `projects`, `user_projects`, `metrics`, `latest_metrics`, `user_metrics`, `roles`.
- Users are identified by `u_email` and `u_id`. Projects are keyed by YouTube `p_id`.

## Navigation

- The Streamlit sidebar in [credify_app.py](mdc:credify_app.py) routes between: Dashboard, Claim Credits, Explore, Settings.

## Implementation guidance

- Prefer adding shared logic in small helpers (e.g., YouTube fetch, ID extraction) and reuse across pages.
- Avoid duplicating dashboards or flows; converge on `credify_app.py` unless there is a strong reason.

